[[Image:Johann Kaspar F<U+00FC>ssli.gif|thumb|right|Johann Kaspar F<U+00FC>ssli]]
'''Johann Kaspar F<U+00FC>ssli''' (9 March 1743 in [[Zurich]] - 4 May 1786 in [[Winterthur]]) was a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[Painting|painter]], [[entomologist]] and [[publisher]].

*He is the son of [[Johann Caspar F<U+00FC>ssli]] (3 January 1706 - 6 May 1782) and Anna Elisabeth Waser.
*He is the brother of [[Henry Fuseli]] (Johann Heinrich F<U+00FC>ssli), (3 December 1745 in Zurich, 26 December 1832 <U+00E0> Zurich).
*He married:
** Verena St<U+00F6>ri in 1770  
** Anna Elisabeth Kilchsperger in 1774.

The only spider species he described (as '''Fuesslin''', 1775) is the ''daddy long-legs spider'', ''[[Pholcus phalangioides]]'', also known as ''cellar spider''.

He is sometimes also written as '''Fuessly'''.

== Publications ==
* ''Verzeichnis der ihm bekannten Schweitzerischen Inseckten'' (1775)
* '' Magazin f<U+00FC>r die Liebhaber der Entomologie'' two tomes (1778-1779)
* ''Neue Magazin f<U+00FC>r Liebhaber der Entomologie'' (1781-1786).

